menu "breadboard: bb_log_http"

config BB_LOG_ROUTES
    bool "Build bb_log HTTP routes (log-level GET/POST)"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_log_http compiles the routes module that exposes
        GET /api/log/level and POST /api/log/level. Disable for headless
        logging-only consumers that compose bb_log_http but don't want the
        routes wired.

        The structured log stream is served separately via bb_data/
        bb_data_http at GET /api/events?topic=log (see bb_log_event's
        "log" bb_data key, B1-1045).

config BB_LOG_SSE_KEEPALIVE_MS
    int "SSE keepalive interval (ms)"
    default 5000
    range 1000 60000
    depends on BB_LOG_ROUTES
    help
        Vestigial — the /api/logs SSE route has been retired. This symbol
        is kept to avoid build breakage on boards that still reference it
        via sdkconfig. It is unused.

endmenu
